description.narrative:
The Center for Promoting Development for Women and Children (DWC) is a Vietnamese non-profit, non-governmental organization established in 2003 under the Decision No. 232 of Vietnam Association for Promoting Education (VAPE). VAPE recognized officially as a social association by Vietnamese Government.

DWC mission is to improve the quality of life for disadvantaged people, especially Women and Children through research, education and training, and to facilitate sustainable development projects and programs, contributing to the National Poverty Reduction Program, and Gender Equality. DWC envisions a Vietnam without poverty where women and children enjoy equal rights and participate in all relevant process of political, economic, cultural and social life.
Main working areas of DWC:
# Promoting sustainable community development: Mobilizing and strengthening community participation with focus on empowerment of women and children;
# Promoting Right Based Approach: Support local authorities (as duty bearers) to fulfil their obligations and localpeople (as rights holders) to claim their rights based on legal laws and policies;
# Conducting trainings to build capacity for local people and local authorities in development related issues;
# Compile and public IEC (Information-Education-Communication) materials to promote human right principles (Non-discrimination and Equality, Participation, Accountability, Transparency, the Rule of Law#);
# Improving living condition for advantaged people through sub-community self-managed development projects at village/community levels focus on decision making rights of villagers and collective livelihood farmer groups towards safe agriculture and environmental protection;
# Provide development related services such as project evaluation, training on gender, women's rights, child rights, participatory tools in project management cycle, facilitation skills, grassroots democracy...
